<div id=3D"P002">
<h2><span style=3D"color:#0000ff;"><strong>Definition</strong></span></h2>

<h3><span style=3D"color:#ff9933;"><strong>Speed</strong></span></h3>

<p>Speed is defined as the rate at which an object is moving (covering a pa=
rticular distance). It is a <strong><em>scalar</em></strong> quantity as it=
 defines only the <strong><em>magnitude</em></strong> and not direction.</p=
>

<p>The SI derived unit for speed is meter per second (<strong>m/s).</strong=
></p>

<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><strong><img alt=3D"Speed is defined as th=
e rate at which an object is moving" src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfro=
nt.net/media/seo_landing_files/image-001-1602174476.png" style=3D"max-width=
: 100%;width: 350px; height: 140px;"></strong></p>

<h3><span style=3D"color:#ff9933;"><strong>Velocity</strong></span></h3>

<p>Velocity is defined as the rate of change of an object=E2=80=99s positio=
n with respect to a frame of reference.</p>

<p>Velocity is a <strong><em>vector</em></strong> quantity as it describes =
both the <strong><em>magnitude</em></strong> and <strong><em>direction</em>=
</strong>.</p>

<p>The SI derived unit for velocity is <strong>meter per second</strong> (<=
strong>m/s).</strong></p>

<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><strong><img alt=3D"Velocity" src=3D"https=
://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfront.net/media/seo_landing_files/image-002-16021745=
29.png" style=3D"max-width: 100%;width: 350px; height: 139px;"></strong></p=
>

<h3><span style=3D"color:#ff9933;"><strong>Acceleration</strong></span></h3=
>

<p>Acceleration is also a <strong><em>vector</em></strong> quantity and is =
defined as the rate of change of velocity with change in time.</p>

<p>The SI derived unit for acceleration is <strong>meter per second squared=
</strong> (<strong>m/s<sup>2</sup>).</strong></p>

<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><strong><img alt=3D"Acceleration is also a=
 vector quantity " src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfront.net/media/seo_l=
anding_files/image-003-1602174590.png" style=3D"max-width: 100%;width: 350p=
x; height: 152px;"></strong></p>

<h3><span style=3D"color:#ff9933;"><strong>Time</strong></span></h3>

<p>A measurable period during which an action/event happens is Time.</p>

<p>The SI derived unit for Time is <strong>seconds (s).</strong></p>

<h3><span style=3D"color:#ff9933;"><strong>International System of Units (S=
I)</strong></span></h3>

<p>International system of units is the modern form of the Metric system. T=
he units listed in this system are used as the standard units of measuremen=
ts in almost every country in the world.</p>

<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><img alt=3D"International System of Units =
(SI)" src=3D"https://d138zd1ktt9iqe.cloudfront.net/media/seo_landing_files/=
image-004-1602174632.png" style=3D"max-width: 100%;width: 350px; height: 36=
7px;"></p>
</div>

