<div id=3D"faqs">
<h2><span style=3D"color:null;"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</=
strong></span></h2>

<div>
<h2>How many weeks are in 6 months?</h2>

<div class=3D"collapsible-area">
<p>Number of days in a year (12 months) =3D 365 (366 once every 4 years)</p=
>

<p>Number of days in a year (6 months) =3D 365/2 =3D 182.5</p>

<p>Number of days in a week =3D 7</p>

<p>So, the number of weeks in 6 months =3D 182.5/7 =3D 26.07 (approximately=
 26 weeks)</p>
</div>
</div>

<div>
<h2>What is the difference between Speed and Velocity?</h2>

<div class=3D"collapsible-area">
<p>Both speed and velocity are the ratio of the distance moved by an object=
 to the time taken for the movement.</p>

<p>But Speed is a <strong><em>Scalar</em></strong> quantity. It considers o=
nly magnitude irrespective of the direction.</p>

<p>Whereas velocity is a <strong><em>Vector</em></strong> quantity and it r=
epresents both magnitude and direction.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div>
<h2>What is the relation between speed and acceleration?</h2>

<div class=3D"collapsible-area">
<p>Acceleration is the rate of change of speed. It denotes the change of sp=
eed with respect to time.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div>
<h2>How many seconds in an hour?</h2>

<div class=3D"collapsible-area">
<p>Number of seconds in a minute =3D 60</p>

<p>Number of minutes in an hour =3D 60</p>

<p>So, number of seconds in an hour =3D 60 =C3=97 60 =3D 3600</p>
</div>
</div>

<div>
<h2>How many minutes in a day?</h2>

<div class=3D"collapsible-area">
<p>Number of minutes in an hour =3D 60</p>

<p>Number of hours in a day =3D 24</p>

<p>So, number of minutes in a day =3D 60 =C3=97 24 =3D 1440</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

